durbin.weka
Class TableFileLoader

java.lang.Object
  durbin.weka.TableFileLoader

public class TableFileLoader
extends java.lang.Object

My own version of CSVLoader. It loads a delimiter separated file into a Table object than converts that to a set of instances. CSV loader is OK, but balks at transposed tables, and I also have table cells that need pre-processing (via Closures) before being saved into the table. This class assumes that all attributes stored in the table file are numeric. These may be converted to nominal by a subsequent filter of some form.

mergeTableColsToInstances

public Instances mergeTableColsToInstances(Table t,
                                           java.lang.String relationName)
                                    throws java.lang.Exception
Merges attributes from a table into an existing set of instances. If attributesToMerge is set then only those attributes will be merged, otherwise all of the attributes in Table t will be merged. The instances are matched by name, so no assumption is made about the order of instances in the original instances and in the Table t.

NOTE: REQUIRES that setMergeData() be called first with the set of Instances to merge AND that the mergeData instances contain an attribute with the label "ID" that gies a unique name for each instance.

Throws:
java.lang.Exception
